instruction: Append the following sentence to make a complete story: "He tried to make sense of it all."
output: He ran his fingers through his thick hair as he tried to make sense of it all. He had been struggling with this problem for too long, and he felt like he was just walking in circles without any progress. It had been days since he started and he still had no answers. He needed to find the key to this mystery, but he was running out of ideas and patience. He had to try something new, something no one else had done before. He had to find an answer. He took a deep breath and started to think of a plan.
